<TITLE> Sahara leaves for Singapore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com)Home minister Sahara Khatun left for Singapore early hours Thursday to undergo medical treatment, said a government spokesperson on Wednesday. She left at 12.50am on a Singapore Airlines flight and will be admitted to the Mount Elizabeth Hospital on arrival there, home ministry public relations officer Shahenur Miah told bdnews24.com. Sahara was accompanied by her personal secretary and a doctor, said an aide to the minister, Md Mosharraf Hussain. The home minister suffered a fall at home on Monday receiving injuries to the right side. She was admitted to hospital and examined by health minister AFM Ruhul Huq. Home ministry officials said state minister for home Tanjim Ahmed was expected to return from a trip to the US by July 3. bdnews
